10.label: Minimum Off Time
10.description: Sets the minimum off time before another heating/cooling cycle can begin to provide compressor short cycle protection.  The thermostat screen will display WAIT when minimum off time is being enforced.

11.label: Minimum Run Time
11.description: Sets the minimum run time before a heating/cooling cycle can turn off to prevent rapid cycling.  Thermostat screen will display "Cool ON" or "Heat ON" while the minimum run time is being enforced.

12.label: Heating Delta Stage 1 ON
12.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 1 heating starts.

13.label: Heating Delta Stage 1 OFF
13.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 1 heating stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 1.

14.label: Heating Delta Stage 2 ON
14.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 2 heating starts.

15.label: Heating Delta Stage 2 OFF
15.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 2 heating stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 2.

16.label: Heating Delta Stage 3 ON
16.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 3 heating starts.

17.label: Heating Delta Stage 3 OFF
17.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 3 heating stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 3.

18.label: Cooling Delta Stage 1 ON
18.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 1 cooling starts.

19.label: Cooling Delta Stage 1 OFF
19.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 1 cooling stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 1.

20.label: Cooling Delta Stage 2 ON
20.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 2 cooling starts.

21.label: Cooling Delta Stage 2 OFF
21.description: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 2 cooling stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 2.

24.label: H/C Delta
24.description: Sets the minimum separation between the heating and cooling setpoints.  Attempts to lower the cooling below the heating setpoint by this amount will PUSH the heating setpoint down to maintain this separation. Same for setting the heating setpoint above the cooling setpoint, it will PUSH the cooling setpoint up to maintain this separation. Settings in F.

29.label: ESM Setpoint--Heating
29.description: Energy Saving Mode (ESM) Setpoints are the setpoints used when the Energy Saving Mode schedule is selected in the Schedule Mode screen (or via Z-Wave control). Setting in F.

30.label: ESM Setpoint--Cooling
30.description: Energy Saving Mode (ESM) Setpoints are the setpoints used when the Energy Saving Mode schedule is selected in the Schedule Mode screen (or via Z-Wave control).

75.label: Fan ON Time
75.description: The fan cycler function cycles the HVAC system fan for an ON period followed by an OFF period continuously. Used to provide minimum air ventilation requirements. When the Fan ON time is set to a value greater than 0, an additional Cycler Fan mode is present when pressing the FAN button on the thermostat.

76.label: Fan OFF Time
76.description: The fan cycler function cycles the HVAC system fan for an ON period followed by an OFF period continuously. Used to provide minimum air ventilation requirements. When the Fan ON time is set to a value greater than 0, an additional Cycler Fan mode is present when pressing the FAN button on the thermostat.

78.label: Aux Heat Enable
78.description: 0 = no aux heat, 1 = aux heat enabled.

132.label: Run Schedule
132.description: Set to 1 if running schedule (RUN is displayed on the thermostat screen).

136.label: Heating 1 Setpoint
136.description:
Heating 1 Setpoint (does this vary with ESM, etc. or is this for the "Hold" setting?
	      Default:
	      HOLD   55F / 13C
	      RUN    60F / xxC
	      ESM    64F / xxC (unless parameter xx has been changed)

137.label: Backlight Timeout
137.description:
Backlight Timeout is the time (in seconds) from the last
	      button press to the backlight going out.  The time-out
	      can be set between 0 and 120
	      seconds.  When set to 0, the backlight will remain
	      always on.
	      Default:  30

138.label: Max Heat Setpoint
138.description:
Sets the maximum heating setpoint value.  Will not ramp
	      or accept setpoints higher than this maximum.
	      Minimum:  55F / xxC
	      Maximum:  90F / xxC
	      Default:  90F / 32C

139.label: Min Cool Setpoint
139.description:
Sets the minimum cooling setpoint value.  Will not ramp
	      or accept setpoints lower than this minimum.
	      Minimum:  60F / xxC
	      Maximum:  99F / xxC
	      Default:  60F / 15C

141.label: Screen Timeout
141.description:
This is the time before any screen reverts to the Minimized
	      Screen (temperature display only), after you stop pushing
	      buttons.  Minimized Screen feature is disabled by setting this
	      time to 0.
	      Default:  0

143.label: Sensor (Internal) Offset
143.description:
The internal temperature sensor can be calibrated to report
	      values different from its actual reading.  The offset can
	      range from -7 degrees to +7 degrees.
	      Default:  0

148.label: Screen Contrast
148.description:
The Screen Contrast sets the contrast level of the LCD display.
	      The contrast can be set between 0 and 20.  If the display
	      is too light, use a higher number.  If dark lines appear on
	      the screen, use a lower number.
	      Default:  10

185.label: Schedule Enable
185.description:
When enabled (set to 1), the local thermostat's scheduler
	      function is enabled.
	      Default:  0

228.label: Schedule Sun-1
228.description:

	      setpoints for Sundays.

	      Byte 1: Hour   (0-23)
	      Byte 2: Minute (0-59)
	      Byte 3: Heat Setpoint (degrees)
	      Byte 4: Cool Setpoint (degrees)
